{
  "texts": [
    "While our primary focus did not revolve around the influence of gender, research in language acquisition has revealed correlations between a child's gender and their language skills.",
    "Specifically, it has been observed that girls often exhibit a slight advantage over boys in this regard (e.g., [46] [47] [48]), and boys are recognized as a group with greater variability [49].",
    "Furthermore, various aspects of communication, including narration style, choice of speech acts, and negotiation methods, appear to differ according to gender [31].",
    "Consequently, we aimed to ensure a balanced representation of gender among our personas.",
    "Since some studies showed differences between input from female and male caregivers, e.g., [50, 51], we balanced the gender of the parent as well."
  ]
}